From: Armbian
Subject: orangepi-r1: DRAM 408 + ZQ/ODT and CPU clock 480MHz

OrangePi R1 is an OrangePi Zero variant on the same H2+ SoC and the same DRAM, so
it gets the same tuning: lower DRAM_CLK 624->408 with ZQ/ODT for stability, and
the 480 MHz small-board CPU clock. (Stock upstream runs DRAM at 624, which is
unstable on these boards.) New Armbian tweak — R1 had no board u-boot patch before.

--- a/configs/orangepi_r1_defconfig
+++ b/configs/orangepi_r1_defconfig
@@ -1,12 +1,15 @@
 CONFIG_ARM=y
 CONFIG_ARCH_SUNXI=y
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-r1"
-CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=624
+CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=408
+CONFIG_DRAM_ZQ=3881979
+CONFIG_DRAM_ODT_EN=y
 CONFIG_SPL=y
 CONFIG_MACH_SUN8I_H3=y
 # CONFIG_VIDEO_DE2 is not set
 CONFIG_SPL_SPI_SUNXI=y
 # CONFIG_SYS_MALLOC_CLEAR_ON_INIT is not set
+CONFIG_SYS_CLK_FREQ=480000000
 CONFIG_CONSOLE_MUX=y
 CONFIG_MTD=y
 CONFIG_SPI_FLASH_WINBOND=y
